-- Taiwan Stocks: Catcher Technology, Simplo, Winbond Electronics
-- B y   W e i y i   L i m
-- 2012-01-17T06:03:41Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-17/taiwan-stock-movers-catcher-technology-winbond-electronics.html
Shares of the following companies
had  unusual  moves in  Taiwan trading . Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the close in Taipei.  The Taiex Index rose 1.7 percent to 7,221.08, the highest
close since Nov. 18.  Catcher Technology Co. (2474)  (2474 TT) gained 5.7 percent to
NT$167.50, the highest close since Nov. 21. The stock was listed
by Morgan Stanley as among the top 25 “high beta” emerging-
market stocks to add during the current rally. High-beta stocks
move the most relative to benchmark indexes.  Simplo Technology Co. (6121)  (6121 TT) surged 6.8 percent to
NT$197, the highest close since Sept. 21, and  Radiant Opto-
electronics Corp. (6176)  (6176 TT) jumped 7 percent to NT$97.90. The
companies are among the key beneficiaries for low-end mainstream
tablet computers, HSBC Holdings Plc said in a report. These
computers are the “new bright spot” for the technology
industry, the brokerage said.  Winbond Electronics Corp. (2344)  (2344 TT) climbed 6.7 percent to
NT$4.30. Winbond was rated new “overweight” at Morgan Stanley,
which said the company is best placed among Taiwan chipmakers.  To contact the reporter on this story:
